headline: General Mills Guidance Cut Puts Earnings Pressure And Dividend Appeal In Focus
summary: General Mills (NYSE:GIS) issued a material downward revision to its full-year 2026 guidance. The company cited worsening sales, profitability, and consumer demand conditions across its core categories. The updated outlook signals increased operational and market headwinds for one of the largest packaged food companies. General Mills, the owner of brands across cereal, snacks, and packaged meals, sits at the center of how households spend on food at home. The guidance cut for 2026 comes at a...
